        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lyndonville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The village officially became independent in 1903, separating itself from the Town of Yates after decades of growth.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lyndonville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Johnson's Creek, winding through the village, once powered early mills and helped shape Lyndonville’s industrial roots.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        17
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lyndonville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Jackson Blood’s cobblestone house, built in the 19th century, earned a spot on the National Register of Historic Places in 2005.",
